Joan Gale https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joan_Gale 0 Joan Gale, born Lorraine Gilmartin, (September 13, 1912 –June 11, 1998) was a vaudeville performer as part of the Gale Sisters and a film actress. She was the twin sister of Jean Gale and performed with a second set of twin sisters (June Gale and Jane Gale) from the same family touring in shows as the Gale Sisters. She married Lou Schreiber, a casting director for 20th Century Fox. She appeared in several Mascot Pictures productions.
